This is screwed up. For those who own Tivo's or fast forward the ads on a dvd this bill would make that illegal. Write your congressman. I for one do not want to be viewing ads and previews on a dvd I paid $20 for. If you give me the dvd for free then I can say you have a case for non fast forwardable dvd's but I'm paying good money for it so screw you MPAA. 
<br />

<br />
I'm not trying to turn this into a political agenda but bills like this one restrict consumer rights. We all lose when something like this gets passed.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-style: italic">On the other hand, if your reaction to something I say boils down to "You didn't choose MY side, make MY choice," well, you're not looking for information, you're looking for someone to tell you how smart you are thinking the way you do. --</span> <span style="font-weight: bold">Ed Stroligo</span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
