                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">UPDATE: Copied verbatim from somewhere else. This doesn't mean the bill will be signed into law but it's moving forward. I'd write to your state senator and oppose to this bill. This has far reaching implications. How far before they introduce commercials in other forms of entertainment that you can't skip past without it being illegal. Once again big business who squander zillions of dollars asking for a break from politicians by screwing the general public. 
<br />

<br />
Now, I don't mind commercials too much. I'm opposed to the fact that they are forcing me to watch something. 99% of the commercials (much like 99% of the TV shows) during breaks are tasteless. I mean, who wouldn't want to kill that damned red headed guy in the ATT commercials. Give me a shotgun full of buckshot and I'd happily unload on his backside. It's why I will never use ATT's collect calling number in emergencies. 
