                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">My (former) boss once asked me the best way of reducing "idiot" calls. (i work on an IT helpdesk).
<br />
My reply:
<br />

<br />
Ritual Sacrifice;
<br />
Each time a user makes a stupid call it gets noted. If they repeatedly make the same stupid calls (this proves they are unable/unwilling to learn) they get publicly sacrificed.
<br />
The advantage;
<br />
Either we run out of idiot users or the rest of them wise up - thus reducing the volume of idiotic calls.
<br />

<br />
Maybe we could have that put through the Senate too? (please!)
<br />

<br />
Btw that was the last time my boss asked me a stupid question reguarding that subject <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
